## 1. The broken recipe (before reconcile)

`source/original/flue-weather/agent.ts` — installed as-is from the `flue/weather` registry entry, fails on current `@flue/runtime` with `ToolLegacyDefinitionError`:

```ts
// source/original/flue-weather/agent.ts  (BROKEN — legacy API)
import { createAgent } from "@flue/runtime";
import { z } from "zod";

export const agent = createAgent({
  name: "weather",
  model: "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
  instructions: "You are a helpful weather assistant.",
  tools: [
    {
      name: "get_weather",
      parameters: z.object({ location: z.string() }),   // ← legacy field name
      async execute(args) {                              // ← legacy signature, no ctx
        const geo = await fetch(
          `https://geocoding-api.open-meteo.com/v1/search?name=${args.location}&count=1`
        ).then(r => r.json());
        const { latitude, longitude } = geo.results[0];
        const wx = await fetch(
          `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=${latitude}&longitude=${longitude}&current=temperature_2m`
        ).then(r => r.json());
        return wx.current;
      },
    },
  ],
});

// legacy recipes also exported a route handler; current @flue/cli owns routing
export const route = { path: "/weather", method: "POST" };
```

Running `npx @flue/cli@latest run weather` against this throws `ToolLegacyDefinitionError` because current `@flue/runtime` expects `defineAgent`/`defineTool` with `input` (not `parameters`) and `run(ctx)` (not `execute(args)`), and no longer accepts a `route` export from an agent module.

