> **Pitfall (verified):** `@hono/zod-validator@0.4.x` was built/tested against zod v3's `safeParseAsync().error` shape. With zod v4 installed, `npm install` prints a peer-dependency warning (`zod@3.x` expected) but the runtime call path still works because `zValidator` only calls `schema.safeParseAsync(value)` and forwards `result` as-is — it never imports zod itself. **It works, but the peer-dep warning is real; don't ignore it as "just noise" without checking the shape of `result.error` for your zod version.** I confirmed `result.error.name === 'ZodError'` and `result.error.message` are both present as own enumerable properties (zod's `ZodError` constructor assigns `this.name`/`this.message` directly), which is why `JSON.stringify` in `c.json(result, 400)` includes them.

